  "title": "Chief Investment Officer (HK and China Desk)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>About Us</strong></u></p>\n<p>We are an integrated asset manager listed in Hong Kong (HKEX: 8313) and headquartered in Singapore, offering integrated solutions across the real estate value chain in the Asia Pacific region.</p>\n<p>Through our investment management services, ZACD has achieved outstanding and consistent investment returns for our clients, building trusted partnerships throughout the years.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct research and analysis on investment opportunities in the <strong>Hong Kong and China markets</strong>, including real estate and other asset classes.</li>\n  <li>Support the preparation of investment proposals, reports, and presentations for internal and external stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Provide advice on market trends, economic developments, and potential investment risks.</li>\n  <li>Assist in the evaluation of new projects or partnerships by compiling financial data and conducting basic feasibility analysis.</li>\n  <li>Maintain databases of market information, investment performance, and regulatory developments in HK and China.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with clients, business partners, and internal teams to facilitate investment transactions and follow-up processes.</li>\n  <li>Participate in business development activities, including investor engagement and administrative coordination.</li>\n  <li>Monitor investment performance and assist with periodic portfolio reviews.</li>\n  <li>Perform other duties as assigned in support of the investment function.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Finance, Economics, Business, or a related field.</li>\n  <li><strong>3 or more years of relevant experience</strong> in investment support, financial analysis, or advisory roles.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with the investment environment and regulations in <strong>China and Hong Kong</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with attention to detail.</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills in <strong>Mandarin and English</strong> (spoken and written), due to market coverage.</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, and basic financial modeling tools.</li>\n</ul>",
